{"id":44608,"date":"2024-01-19T09:56:00","date_gmt":"2024-01-19T04:26:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=44608"},"modified":"2023-04-20T10:57:19","modified_gmt":"2023-04-20T05:27:19","slug":"designing-a-small-home-library","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/designing-a-small-home-library\/","title":{"rendered":"Small Home Library: Designing The Perfect Reading Space!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Want a small home library at home but don&#8217;t know how to get started? Here&#8217;s a brief guide to designing the perfect small cosy home library. Read along!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>A small home library is a collection of books you keep in your home, whether in a designated bookshelf or spread throughout your living space. While it may seem like a small addition to your home, a home library can significantly impact your personal and intellectual growth.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this blog post, we&#8217;ll explore why having a small home library is important and how it can benefit you in various ways. Whether you&#8217;re a book lover looking to expand your collection or someone who wants to create a cosy and inviting atmosphere in your home, this post is for you. So, let&#8217;s dive in and understand how you can design, decorate and maintain a small home library.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choosing the Right Room or Space for Your Home Library<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right room or space for your home library is crucial. Ideally, you want an area that is quiet, comfortable, and conducive to reading. If you have a spare room, that&#8217;s a great option for a dedicated reading space. But if you don&#8217;t, let that not stop you from creating a home library.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Look for small or awkward spaces that can be transformed into a cosy <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/reading-nook\/\">reading nook<\/a>, such as a corner of a room or under a staircase. You can also use multi-purpose rooms, such as a home office or living room, as a home library by incorporating shelving and seating into the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104619\/choosing-right-small-home-library-room.jpg\" alt=\"Choosing right small home library room\" class=\"wp-image-44616\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104619\/choosing-right-small-home-library-room.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104619\/choosing-right-small-home-library-room-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104619\/choosing-right-small-home-library-room-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104619\/choosing-right-small-home-library-room-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Choosing the perfect small home library space is the first step!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choosing the Right Shelving for Your Space and Books<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Choosing the right shelving for your space and books is vital for functionality and aesthetics. Built-in shelves can be an excellent option for maximising space and creating a seamless look. They can also be customised to fit the specific dimensions of your room.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Floating shelves can add visual interest and storage without taking up too much room and create a unique focal point. Free-standing shelves can also be used to divide a room or draw attention to them. Get creative with your shelving by using it for book storage and displaying decorative items, such as plants, art, and collectibles.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104614\/choosing-right-shelving-for-your-small-home-library.jpg\" alt=\"Choosing right shelving for your small home library\" class=\"wp-image-44615\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104614\/choosing-right-shelving-for-your-small-home-library.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104614\/choosing-right-shelving-for-your-small-home-library-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104614\/choosing-right-shelving-for-your-small-home-library-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104614\/choosing-right-shelving-for-your-small-home-library-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>A small home library that displays your favourite decor pieces<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choosing the Right Type of Seating For Your Small Cosy Home Library<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Comfortable seating is critical for any home library. You want to create a cosy, inviting space to curl up with a good book and relax. Consider choosing comfortable seating, such as armchairs, bean bags, or floor cushions. Consider incorporating seating into the shelving, such as built-in benches or window seats, if you have limited space. You can also use a cosy rug or throw pillows to create a comfortable reading nook.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104608\/small-home-library-seating-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"small home library seating ideas\" class=\"wp-image-44614\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104608\/small-home-library-seating-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104608\/small-home-library-seating-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104608\/small-home-library-seating-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104608\/small-home-library-seating-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Finding the appropriate kind of seating for your small home reading room<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Choosing the Right Type of Lighting (Table Lamps, Floor Lamps, Pendant Lights)<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Proper lighting is essential for any home library. You want to create a warm and inviting atmosphere conducive to reading. Table lamps, floor lamps, and pendant lights can all be used to create a cosy atmosphere. If you have limited space, consider using <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/8-lighting-ideas-for-your-home\/\">creative lighting solutions<\/a>, such as string lights or recessed lighting. Make sure to consider natural lighting, such as windows or skylights, and how it can enhance the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104602\/small-home-library-lighting-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"small home library lighting ideas\" class=\"wp-image-44613\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104602\/small-home-library-lighting-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104602\/small-home-library-lighting-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104602\/small-home-library-lighting-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104602\/small-home-library-lighting-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Reading chair designs for your small library at home.\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Ergonomic study room interiors perfect for indian homes\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/15154220\/ergonomic-study-room-interiors-perfect-for-indian-homes-scaled.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Adding Personal Touches to Your Home Library:<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Personal touches make your home library feel like your own. Consider adding plants, artwork, and other decorative items that reflect your personality and interests. You can also use cosmetic storage solutions, such as baskets or decorative boxes, to store and display items. Get creative with storing and displaying your collectibles and other objects using shelving or other storage solutions. You can also use rugs, curtains, or other textiles to add texture and visual interest to the space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104556\/small-home-library-with-personal-touches.jpg\" alt=\"Small home library with personal touches\" class=\"wp-image-44612\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104556\/small-home-library-with-personal-touches.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104556\/small-home-library-with-personal-touches-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104556\/small-home-library-with-personal-touches-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104556\/small-home-library-with-personal-touches-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Indoor plants and decor for your wall-mounted small library at home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Tips for Organising Your Small Home Library:<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Organising your book collection is key to making your home library functional and enjoyable. Get creative with categorising and arranging your books, using colour or genre to create a visually pleasing display. Incorporating technology for organisation and storage, such as an e-reader or a book-tracking app, can also be helpful. You can also use decorative bookends or baskets to keep your books organised and looking neat.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104551\/small-home-library-organisation-tips.jpg\" alt=\"Small home library organisation tips\" class=\"wp-image-44611\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104551\/small-home-library-organisation-tips.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104551\/small-home-library-organisation-tips-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104551\/small-home-library-organisation-tips-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/04\/20104551\/small-home-library-organisation-tips-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption>Visually pleasing small at-home library for the perfect weekend unwinder!\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In conclusion, a small home library can be a wonderful addition to any home. By carefully considering the location, shelving, seating, lighting, decor, and organisation, you can create a cosy and inviting space to relax and read. Don&#8217;t be afraid to get creative and make your home library truly your own, incorporating personal touches and unique design elements. With some planning and effort, you can create a space you&#8217;ll love to spend time in. Connect with our expert designers at <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/\">DesignCafe<\/a> to get started on the small home library of your dreams<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the meantime, check out our blogs on:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/reading-chair-designs\/\">Reading Chair Designs For Your Home<\/a><\/li><li><a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/book-rack-design-ideas\/\">Modern Book Rack Designs For Your Home<\/a><\/li><\/ul>\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?Productive Spaces For An Ideal Home<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutionsSmart modular solutions for Indian homes<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n  